The paper deals with the problem of analyzing infinite-state systems using tree automata, which is a topic that falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of lattices to represent complex domains and related operations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). The discussion of efficient algorithms for computing sets of reachable states suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
